column5: ~~~~Was out on Sunday out of Sibs, headed out to my usual starting spot in 38' N. of George, and the bait and Perch were solid from 12' down, rough time getting our lures down without being hit, on the way down, came home with 24 Jumbos releasing over 200, here my buddy Slug with his largest
Lots of boats out on K bay the last week or so. I'm sure the perch derby has contributed to the numbers some as well as the nice weather.
Good to hear they are starting to stack up, I am up at Dalrymple all week I may just head down for some green gold.
